title: BREAKING: ‘NOT A DRILL’ Nevada officials tell locals to evacuate as dam threatens to burst
text:
BREAKING: ‘NOT A DRILL’ Nevada officials tell locals to evacuate as dam threatens to burst BREAKING: ‘NOT A DRILL’ Nevada officials tell locals to evacuate as dam threatens to burst RENO’S National weather service has told East Dayton residents to evacuate immediately as a damn threatens to burst, flooding the area. PUBLISHED: 22:05, Tue, Feb 21, 2017 | UPDATED: 22:14, Tue, Feb 21, 2017 
Officials say the dam will fail ‘imminently’– unleashing several feet of water across scores of streets. 
Taking to twitter NWS Reno said “URGENT: Retention basin above East Dayton, NV failing.” 
“THIS IS NOT A DRILL”. 
While it is unclear how many people live in the affected area census data claims 50,000 live in the region. 
More to follow...
